for New Orleans.</i>

236
00:21:14,332 --> 00:21:16,266
<i>Lance, on the forward fifties...</i>

237
00:21:16,367 --> 00:21:19,097
<i>was a famous surfer
from the beaches south of L. A.</i>

238
00:21:19,204 --> 00:21:23,038
<i>To look at him, you wouldn't believe
he'd ever fired a weapon in his life.</i>

239
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:29,107
<i>Clean- Mr. Clean- was
from some South Bronx shit-hole...</i>

240
00:21:29,214 --> 00:21:31,375
<i>and I think the light
and the space of Vietnam...</i>

241
00:21:31,483 --> 00:21:35,078
<i>really put the zap on his head.</i>

242
00:21:36,488 --> 00:21:39,116
<i>Then there was Phillips,
the chief.</i>

243
00:21:39,224 --> 00:21:43,160
<i>It might have been my mission, but
it sure as shit was the chief's boat.</i>

244
00:21:43,261 --> 00:21:45,195
There's about two points
where we can draw enough water...

245
00:21:45,296 --> 00:21:47,696
to get into the Nung River.

246
00:21:47,799 --> 00:21:51,963
They're both hot.
Belong to Charlie.

247
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:54,470
Don't worry about it.

248
00:21:54,572 --> 00:21:57,666
Don't smoke.

249
00:21:57,775 --> 00:22:00,938
You know, I've pulled
a few special ops in here.

250
00:22:01,045 --> 00:22:03,639
About six months ago...

251
00:22:03,748 --> 00:22:08,048
I took a man who was going up
past the bridge at Do Lung.

252
00:22:08,153 --> 00:22:10,849
He was regular army too.

253
00:22:12,857 --> 00:22:16,293
Heard he shot himself
in the head.

254
00:22:24,202 --> 00:22:28,104
<i>At first I thought
they handed me the wrong dossier.</i>

255
00:22:28,206 --> 00:22:30,766
<i>I couldn't believe
they wanted this man dead.</i>

256
00:22:32,410 --> 00:22:35,311
<i>Third-generation West Point,
top of his class.</i>

257
00:22:35,413 --> 00:22:39,645
<i>Korea, Airborne,
about a thousand decorations.</i>

258
00:22:39,751 --> 00:22:41,742
<i>Et cetera, et cetera.</i>

259
00:22:44,322 --> 00:22:49,259
<i>I'd heard his voice on the tape,
and it really put the hook in me...</i>

260
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:53,956
<i>but I couldn't connect up
that voice with this man.</i>

261
00:23:00,071 --> 00:23:03,939
<i>Like they said,
he had an impressive career.</i>

262
00:23:04,042 --> 00:23:08,945
<i>Maybe too impressive.
I mean, perfect.</i>

263
00:23:09,047 --> 00:23:13,279
<i>He was being groomed for one of
the top slots in the corporation-</i>

264
00:23:13,384 --> 00:23:16,683
<i>general, chief of staff,
anything.</i>

265
00:23:18,389 --> 00:23:22,416
<i>In 1964, he returned from a tour
with Advisory Command in Vietnam...</i>

266
00:23:22,527 --> 00:23:24,893
<i>and things started to slip.</i>

267
00:23:24,996 --> 00:23:27,089
<i>His report to
the Joint Chiefs of Staff...</i>

268
00:23:27,198 --> 00:23:29,632
<i>and Lyndon Johnson was restricted.</i>

269
00:23:31,336 --> 00:23:35,102
<i>Seems they didn't dig
what he had to tell them.</i>

270
00:23:35,206 --> 00:23:38,141
<i>During the next few months, he
made three requests for transfer...</i>

271
00:23:38,243 --> 00:23:43,306
<i>to Airborne training, Fort Benning,
Georgia, and was finally accepted.</i>

272
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:48,450
<i>Airborne?</i>

273
00:23:50,388 --> 00:23:53,050
<i>He was 38 years old.</i>

274
00:23:54,158 --> 00:23:56,422
<i>Why the fuck would he do that?</i>

275
00:23:58,763 --> 00:24:03,029
<i>1966, joins Special Forces...</i>

276
00:24:03,134 --> 00:24:05,159
<i>returns to Vietnam.</i>

277
00:24:05,436 --> 00:24:07,427
Hey, what's that?

278
00:24:07,538 --> 00:24:10,029
- Arc light.
- What's up?

279
00:24:10,141 --> 00:24:12,701
- B-52 strike.
- Yeah?

280
00:24:12,810 --> 00:24:14,710
- What's that?
- Arc light.

281
00:24:14,812 --> 00:24:17,781
I hate that. Every time I hear that,
something terrible happens.

282
00:24:17,882 --> 00:24:19,782
Charlie don't never
see 'em or hear 'em, man.

283
00:24:19,884 --> 00:24:21,112
There they are.

284
00:24:21,219 --> 00:24:23,517
Concussion will suck the air
out of your damn lungs.

285
00:24:23,621 --> 00:24:25,646
Something terrible
is gonna happen.

286
00:24:25,757 --> 00:24:29,386
Smoke! Secondary burning.

287
00:24:29,494 --> 00:24:32,019
Hueys over there. Lots of Hueys.

288
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:35,031
Let's have a look, Chief.

289
00:24:35,133 --> 00:24:38,728
<i>It was the Air-Cav.
First of the Ninth-</i>

290
00:24:38,836 --> 00:24:39,666
That's them.

291
00:24:39,771 --> 00:24:42,672
<i>our escorts to the mouth
of the Nung River.</i>

292
00:24:42,774 --> 00:24:46,642
<i>But they were supposed to be waiting
for us another 30 kilometers ahead.</i>

293
00:24:46,744 --> 00:24:51,909
<i>Well, Air Mobile.
Those boys just couldn't stay put.</i>

294
00:25:03,594 --> 00:25:06,563
Hey, kid, come on.
Get down. Come on.

295
00:25:17,608 --> 00:25:20,509
<i>First of the Ninth was
an old cavalry division...</i>

296
00:25:20,611 --> 00:25:22,511
<i>that had cashed in its horses
for choppers...</i>

297
00:25:22,613 --> 00:25:26,515
<i>and gone tear-assing around
'Nam looking for the shit.</i>

298
00:25:26,617 --> 00:25:31,179
<i>They'd given Charlie
a few surprises in their time here.</i>

299
00:25:31,289 --> 00:25:36,124
<i>What they were mopping up now hadn't
even happened yet an hour ago.</i>

300
00:25:36,227 --> 00:25:38,525
Just keeping running by.
We're for television.

301
00:25:38,629 --> 00:25:40,927
Don't look at the camera.
Just keep- Go on. Keep going.

302
00:25:41,032 --> 00:25:42,932
This is for television.
Don't look at the camera.

303
00:25:43,034 --> 00:25:46,333
Just go by like you're fighting,
like you're fighting.

304
00:25:46,437 --> 00:25:49,964
Don't look at the camera.
It's for television. Just go through.

305
00:25:50,074 --> 00:25:52,065
Just go by. Keep on going.

306
00:25:52,176 --> 00:25:54,303
Keep going. Don't look at the camera.
Go on. Keep going.

307
00:25:54,412 --> 00:25:56,277
All right, come on. Go.

308
00:26:01,352 --> 00:26:03,320
Right here. Yes.
Over here. Over here.

309
00:26:17,301 --> 00:26:19,701
Where can I find the CO?

310
00:26:19,804 --> 00:26:23,968
That's the colonel comin' down!

311
00:26:32,216 --> 00:26:34,878
The CO's on that chopper.

312
00:26:57,141 --> 00:27:00,668
Lieutenant, bomb that tree line
back about 100 yards!

313
00:27:00,778 --> 00:27:03,906
- Give me some room to breathe!
- Yes, sir!

314
00:27:08,653 --> 00:27:09,915
Body cards!

315
00:27:10,021 --> 00:27:12,046
- Sir?
- Bring my body cards!

316
00:27:12,156 --> 00:27:14,056
Yes, sir!

317
00:27:16,627 --> 00:27:19,892
I'm the Fourth Tank commander.
I got five tanks broken down.

318
00:27:19,997 --> 00:27:23,160
We're all right with the tanks.
It's all right, Captain.

319
00:27:23,267 --> 00:27:24,529
Captain Willard!

320
00:27:24,635 --> 00:27:28,036
I carry priority papers from
Com-Sec Intelligence, II Corps.

321
00:27:28,139 --> 00:27:30,073
I understand Nha Trang
has briefed you...

322
00:27:30,174 --> 00:27:32,074
on the requirements of my mission.

323
00:27:32,176 --> 00:27:34,770
What mission?
I haven't heard from Nha Trang.

324
00:27:34,879 --> 00:27:37,814
Sir, your unit is supposed
to escort us into the Nung!

325
00:27:37,915 --> 00:27:40,076
- We'll see what we can do.
- Colonel!

326
00:27:40,184 --> 00:27:44,951
But just stay out of my way
until this is done, Captain.

327
00:27:47,358 --> 00:27:50,225
All right, let's see what we have.
Let's see what we have.

328
00:27:50,328 --> 00:27:55,391
A two of spades, three of spades,
four of diamonds...

329
00:27:55,500 --> 00:27:58,128
six of clubs, eight of spades.

330
00:27:58,236 --> 00:28:01,262
There isn't one worth a jack
in the whole bunch.

331
00:28:01,372 --> 00:28:04,307
Four of diamonds.

332
00:28:04,408 --> 00:28:08,139
- Hey, Captain, what's that?
- Death cards!

333
00:28:08,246 --> 00:28:11,545
- What?
- Death cards!

334
00:28:11,649 --> 00:28:13,981
- Death?
- Lets Charlie know who did this.

335
00:28:17,555 --> 00:28:20,388
<i>- Cheer up, son.
- We will not hurt or harm you.</i>

336
00:28:20,491 --> 00:28:24,257
- Fire in the hole!
- Fire in the hole!

337
00:28:24,529 --> 00:28:27,987
<i>This is an area
that is controlled...</i>

338
00:28:28,099 --> 00:28:30,499
<i>by the Vietcong
and North Vietnamese.</i>

339
00:28:30,601 --> 00:28:32,501
Jim.

340
00:28:36,574 --> 00:28:39,805
<i>We are here to help you.</i>

341
00:28:40,945 --> 00:28:44,904
<i>- We extend a welcome hand...
- Come on.</i>

342
00:28:45,016 --> 00:28:47,075
<i>- to those who would like to return...
- Everybody in?</i>

343
00:28:47,184 --> 00:28:51,518
<i>to the arms of
the South Vietnamese government.</i>

344
00:28:51,622 --> 00:28:55,023
Get in. Hurry up.

345
00:28:56,127 --> 00:28:57,822
Move it out.

346
00:28:57,929 --> 00:29:00,454
<i>This is an area
that is controlled...</i>

347
00:29:00,565 --> 00:29:03,159
<i>by the Vietcong
and North Vietnamese.</i>

348
00:29:03,267 --> 00:29:08,432
Hey! What's this?
What is this?

349
00:29:08,539 --> 00:29:11,235
This man's hurt
pretty bad, sir.

350
00:29:11,342 --> 00:29:14,778
About the only thing that's holding
his guts in, sir, is that pot lid.

351
00:29:14,879 --> 00:29:17,279
Yeah? What do you have to say?

352
00:29:17,381 --> 00:29:23,217
This soldier is dirty VC. He wants
water. He can drink paddy water.

353
00:29:23,321 --> 00:29:26,722
Get outta here!
Give me that canteen.

354
00:29:26,824 --> 00:29:29,952
- He's VC!
- Any man that's brave enough to-

355
00:29:30,061 --> 00:29:32,655
Get outta here!
I'll kick your fuckin' ass!

356
00:29:32,763 --> 00:29:34,890
He killed a lot of our people!

357
00:29:34,999 --> 00:29:37,092
Any man brave enough
to fight with his guts...

358
00:29:37,201 --> 00:29:39,192
strapped on him
can drink from my canteen.

359
00:29:39,303 --> 00:29:43,364
Hey, Colonel, I think one of those
sailors is Lance Johnson, the surfer.

360
00:29:43,474 --> 00:29:47,308
- Where? Here? You sure?
- Down there.

361
00:29:47,411 --> 00:29:49,402
Yeah? Here.

362
00:29:49,513 --> 00:29:52,414
Repeat. We have a body count.
We have-

363
00:29:55,086 --> 00:29:57,145
What's your name, sailor?

364
00:29:57,254 --> 00:30:00,087
- Gunner's Mate Third Class Johnson.
- Gunner's Mate Third Class-

365
00:30:00,191 --> 00:30:04,287
- Lance Johnson, the surfer?
- Yes, sir.

366
00:30:04,395 --> 00:30:08,525
It's an honor to meet you. I've
admired your nose riding for years.

367
00:30:08,633 --> 00:30:11,500
I like your cutback too. I think
you have the best cutback there is.

368
00:30:11,602 --> 00:30:14,264
- Thank you, sir.
- You can cut out the "sir" crap.

369
00:30:14,372 --> 00:30:16,363
I'm Bill Kilgore.
I'm a goofy foot.

370
00:30:16,474 --> 00:30:18,374
- This guy with ya?
- Yeah.

371
00:30:18,476 --> 00:30:20,307
I want you to meet some guys.

372
00:30:20,411 --> 00:30:22,311
- This is Mike from San Diego.
- Far out.

373
00:30:22,413 --> 00:30:25,280
- Johnny from Malibu. Solid surfers.
- John, hi. Far out.

374
00:30:25,383 --> 00:30:27,510
None of us are anywhere
near your class though.

375
00:30:27,618 --> 00:30:29,051
No way.

376
00:30:29,153 --> 00:30:33,055
We do a lot of surfing around here.
I like to finish operations early.

377
00:30:33,157 --> 00:30:35,523
Fly down to Yung Tau
for the evening glass.

378
00:30:35,626 --> 00:30:38,060
Been riding since you got here?

379
00:30:38,162 --> 00:30:40,756
No way. I haven't surfed
since I been here.

380
00:30:40,865 --> 00:30:43,265
Through Christ, our Lord...

381
00:30:43,367 --> 00:30:45,460
from Whom
all good things come...

382
00:30:45,569 --> 00:30:48,129
through Him in the unity
of the Holy Spirit.

383
00:30:48,239 --> 00:30:51,106
All glory and honor
is Yours, Almighty Father.

384
00:30:51,208 --> 00:30:53,676
Let us bring
our iniquities to the Father...

385
00:30:53,778 --> 00:30:55,712
in the words our Savior gave us.

386
00:30:55,813 --> 00:31:00,750
Our Father, Who art in heaven,
hallowed be Thy name.

387
00:31:00,851 --> 00:31:05,515
Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done
on earth as it is in heaven.

388
00:31:05,623 --> 00:31:08,421
Give us this day
our daily bread...

389
00:31:08,526 --> 00:31:10,426
and forgive us our trespasses...

390
00:31:10,528 --> 00:31:12,655
<i>as we forgive those
who trespass against us.</i>

391
00:31:12,763 --> 00:31:16,392
<i>Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.</i>

392
00:31:25,443 --> 00:31:29,209
<i>Kilgore had had a pretty
good day for himself.</i>

393
00:31:29,313 --> 00:31:31,440
<i>They choppered in
the T-bones and the beer...</i>

394
00:31:31,549 --> 00:31:34,848
<i>and turned the LZ
into a beach party.</i>

395
00:31:34,952 --> 00:31:37,921
<i>The more they tried
to make it just like home...</i>

396
00:31:38,022 --> 00:31:40,650
<i>the more they made
everybody miss it.</i>

397
00:31:40,758 --> 00:31:43,955
Make my meat rare-
rare but not cold.

398
00:31:49,967 --> 00:31:53,198
<i>Well, he wasn't
a bad officer, I guess.</i>

399
00:31:53,304 --> 00:31:56,796
<i>He loved his boys,
and you felt safe with him.</i>

400
00:31:56,907 --> 00:32:00,206
<i>He was one of those guys that
had that weird light around him.</i>

401
00:32:00,311 --> 00:32:04,077
<i>You just knew he wasn't gonna
get so much as a scratch here.</i>

402
00:32:04,181 --> 00:32:08,049
What happened to your mission?
Nha Trang forget all about you?

403
00:32:16,093 --> 00:32:19,153
Airborne.

404
00:32:19,263 --> 00:32:22,755
Sir, two places we can
get into the river.

405
00:32:22,867 --> 00:32:25,859
- Yeah.
- Here and here.

406
00:32:25,970 --> 00:32:30,839
It's a pretty wide delta, but these
are the only two spots I'm sure of.

407
00:32:30,941 --> 00:32:33,967
That village you're pointing at
is kind of hairy.

408
00:32:34,078 --> 00:32:36,410
- What do you mean "hairy," sir?
- It's hairy.

409
00:32:36,514 --> 00:32:38,414
Got some pretty heavy ordnance.

410
00:32:38,516 --> 00:32:40,882
I lost a few recon ships
in there now and again.

411
00:32:40,985 --> 00:32:44,216
What's the name of
that goddamn village? Vin Drin-

412
00:32:44,321 --> 00:32:46,687
- Dop.
- Dop or Lop?

413
00:32:46,791 --> 00:32:50,420
Damn gook names
all sound the same.

414
00:32:50,528 --> 00:32:53,520
Mike, you know anything about
this point at Vin Drin Dop?

415
00:32:53,631 --> 00:32:55,531
That's a fantastic peak.

416
00:32:55,633 --> 00:32:58,067
- Peak?
- About six foot.

417
00:32:58,169 --> 00:33:01,866
It's an outstanding peak. It's got
both the long right and left slide...

418
00:33:01,972 --> 00:33:04,167
with a bowl section
that's unbelievable.

419
00:33:04,275 --> 00:33:06,675
It's just tube city.

420
00:33:09,446 --> 00:33:11,914
Why didn't you tell me
that before? A good peak.

421
00:33:12,016 --> 00:33:14,712
There aren't any good peaks
in this whole shitty country.

422
00:33:14,819 --> 00:33:16,719
It's all goddamn beach break.

423
00:33:16,821 --> 00:33:19,756
It's really hairy in there.
That's where we lost McDonald.

424
00:33:19,857 --> 00:33:24,089
They shot the hell out of us there.
That's Charlie's point.

425
00:33:24,195 --> 00:33:26,629
Sir, we can go in there
tomorrow at dawn.

426
00:33:26,730 --> 00:33:28,789
There's always a good
offshore breeze in the morning.

427
00:33:28,899 --> 00:33:30,799
We may not be able
to get the boat in.

428
00:33:30,901 --> 00:33:34,894
The draft at the mouth of
that river may be too shallow.

429
00:33:35,005 --> 00:33:37,974
We'll pick your boat up and put it
down like a baby where you want it.

430
00:33:38,075 --> 00:33:40,566
This is the First of the Ninth,
Air-Cav, son.

431
00:33:40,678 --> 00:33:45,012
Air mobile! I can take that point
and hold it as long as I like.

432
00:33:45,115 --> 00:33:48,141
You can get anyplace up that river
that suits you, young Captain.

433
00:33:48,252 --> 00:33:50,652
Hell, a six-foot peak.

434
00:33:51,889 --> 00:33:53,823
Take a gunship
back to the division.

435
00:33:53,924 --> 00:33:55,983
Lance, go with Mike and let him
pick out a board for you.

436
00:33:56,093 --> 00:33:58,254
Bring me my Yater Spoon,
the eight-six.

437
00:33:58,362 --> 00:34:00,262
- I don't know, sir-
- What is it, soldier?

438
00:34:00,364 --> 00:34:03,424
It's hairy in there.
It's Charlie's point.

439
00:34:03,534 --> 00:34:05,661
Charlie don't surf!

440
00:34:28,792 --> 00:34:32,751
Hey, Jesus, Clean, you ain't
gonna believe this. Look.

441
00:34:33,864 --> 00:34:36,765
Hey, man!
They're pickin' up the boat!

442
00:34:39,970 --> 00:34:43,872
- How are you feeling, Jimmy?
- Like a mean motherfucker, sir!

443
00:34:45,509 --> 00:34:47,477
All right, son, let 'er rip.

444
00:34:47,578 --> 00:34:50,342
Let's go!

445
00:36:12,763 --> 00:36:16,563
I never have got used to a light
board. I can't get used to one.

446
00:36:16,667 --> 00:36:19,568
- I'm used to a heavy board.
- I know, it's a real drag.

447
00:36:19,670 --> 00:36:22,298
- You prefer a heavy or light board?
- Heavier.

448
00:36:22,406 --> 00:36:24,306
- Really?
- Yeah!

449
00:36:24,408 --> 00:36:27,070
I thought all the young guys
like lighter boards.

450
00:36:27,177 --> 00:36:30,271
<i>- You can't ride the nose on those.
- Big Duke Six.</i>

451
00:36:30,381 --> 00:36:32,042
This is Eagle Thrust Seven.
We've got it spotted.

452
00:36:32,149 --> 00:36:33,707
<i>Duke Six to Eagle Thrust.</i>

453
00:36:33,817 --> 00:36:37,253
Put on heading two-seven-zero.
Assume attack formation.

454
00:36:37,354 --> 00:36:39,720
<i>That's a roger, Big Duke.
We're going in.</i>

455
00:36:39,823 --> 00:36:43,884
Hey, Lance, we'll come in
low out of the rising sun.

456
00:36:43,994 --> 00:36:46,462
About a mile out,
we'll put on the music.

457
00:36:46,563 --> 00:36:48,929
- Music?
- Yeah, I use Wagner.

458
00:36:49,033 --> 00:36:53,163
Scares the hell out of the slopes.
My boys love it.

459
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:55,602
